@startuml
title Séquence métier — Relancer une notification en échec (Notification)
' ------------------------------------------------------------------
' Style impression A4 (PFE FSEG) — lisibilité : polices ~11–12 pt visibles,
' DPI 240, retour à la ligne des messages. Inclure juste après la ligne title.
' Export PNG pour Word/LaTeX : viser largeur <= zone utile A4 (~17 cm).
' ------------------------------------------------------------------
scale max 1550 width
skinparam dpi 240
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam HyperlinkUnderline false

skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam titleFontSize 16
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam arrowThickness 1.25
skinparam wrapWidth 220
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam LegendFontSize 10
skinparam footerFontSize 10
skinparam headerFontSize 10

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 14
skinparam BoxPadding 8
skinparam LifeLineBorderColor #444444
skinparam LifeLineBackgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ArrowColor #222222
skinparam ActorBorderColor #222222
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #EEF6FF
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF

skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #F8F8F8
skinparam EntityBackgroundColor #F8FFF8
skinparam ControlBackgroundColor #FFF8F0
skinparam BoundaryBackgroundColor #F5F5FF
actor Admin as admin
boundary "Administration" as UI
control "Contrôleur" as Svc
entity "Base de données" as DB
queue "BullMQ : send-email" as Queue

admin -> UI: Consulter les notifications en échec (file d’échec)
UI -> Svc: GET /api/admin/failed-notifications
Svc -> DB: Trouver les FailedWorkflowEvents (workflowType="notification", resolved=false)
DB --> Svc: events
Svc --> UI: list
UI --> admin: Afficher les événements d’e-mail en échec

admin -> UI: Choisir un événement, cliquer « Relancer »
UI -> Svc: POST /api/admin/retry-notification { eventId }

Svc -> DB: Trouver le FailedWorkflowEvent par id
DB --> Svc: event

alt event.resolved == false
  Svc -> DB: Trouver la notification d’origine via données.notificationId
  DB --> Svc: notification (if exists)
  
  alt notification existe
    Svc -> Queue: enqueueEmailForNotification(notificationId) (sans bloquer)
    Svc -> DB: Mettre à jour event.resolved = true, resolvedBy = admin.id, resolvedAt = now()
    Svc -> DB: AuditLog (RETRY_NOTIFICATION_SUCCESS)
    Svc --> UI: 200
    UI --> admin: Relance demandée (envoi e-mail)
  else notification absente / données invalides
    Svc -> DB: Mettre à jour event.resolved = true (pas de relance possible)
    Svc --> UI: 200 Événement clôturé (notification introuvable)
  end
else
  Svc --> UI: 400 Déjà clôturé
end

note right of Svc
  - Failed notifications are stored in `FailedWorkflowEvent` with `workflowType="notification"`
  - Payload contient au minimum `notificationId` (le reste est optionnel selon les versions)
  - La relance est effectuée sans bloquer via `enqueueEmailForNotification(notificationId)`
  - L’événement est marqué `resolved=true` pour éviter les doublons
end note
@enduml
